{{Quote|When the durkiis are soothed, they are very docile. But when they are angry, there is no beast in all of Tammuz-an that can match their viciousness!|Ko Zatec-Cha|<ref name="TNK">{{DroidsCite|The New King}}</ref>}}
A '''durkii''' was a large [[Color/Legends|purple]] bipedal [[Reptile/Legends|reptilian]] monster known for fits of rage when effected with [[Kleex/Legends|kleex]].

[[Luminara Unduli/Legends|Luminara Unduli]] defeated a durkii in the [[Arena of Doom]] using no [[The Force/Legends|Force]] [[Force power/Legends|abilities]], but only simple physics.<ref name="V">{{CWACite|8|Versus (comic story)}}</ref>

The evil [[Vizier/Legends|vizier]] [[Ko Zatec-Cha]] kept a hungry durkii at the bottom of a deep dungeon pit on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tammuz-an/Legends|Tammuz-an]]. He cast the royal [[Prince/Legends|prince]] [[Mon Julpa]] and his friends into the pit in the hope that the durkii would destroy them. The [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] quelled the creature's temper by removing a parasitic insect known as a kleex from its scaly hide.<ref name="TNK" />

